Am I Biased?
For each of the following scenarios, call out the potential biases in the proposed experiment. Do your best to try to discover not only the bias, but the initial design. There is plenty of room for interpretation here, so make sure to state what assumptions you're making.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
You're testing advertising emails for a bathing suit company and you test one version of the email in February and the other in May.
Condition Bias:  February in Hong Kong is Chinese new year where married adult give to who have married, therefore people has more buying power in February than in May
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
You open a clinic to treat anxiety and find that the people who visit show a higher rate of anxiety than the general population.
Selection Bias : There exists people who has the same level of anxiety people do not go to clinic or Simpson’s paradox do occurs 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
You launch a new ad billboard based campaign and see an increase in website visits in the first week.
Condition Bias:  It is normal that the first week of website visits will be higher, so that it can’t conclude that the new ad billboard works.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

You launch a loyalty program but see no change in visits in the first week.
Condition Bias:  The program of loyalty program may involve new user, and time is required to monitor the process. Even though for existing user, the first week may not reflects the loyalty program yet

